title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> be the set of all elements <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \in \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> which are algebraic over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:strong>Claim 1:</fr:strong> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}\subseteq  L]]></fr:tex>. We see that for any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> the polynomial <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(x-a)\in \mathbb {F}[x]]]></fr:tex> has a root (namely <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>) which belongs to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex>. Hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  a\in \mathbb {F}\ldotp  a\in  L]]></fr:tex>, i.e., <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}\subseteq  L]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:strong>Claim 2:</fr:strong> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is closed under field operations. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta \in \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> be algebraic over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}(\alpha ,\beta )/\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is an algebraic extension (since <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0014.xml"
addr="nt-0014"
title="An extension is finite iff it is finitely-generated by algebraic elements">An extension is finite iff it is finitely-generated by algebraic elements</fr:link>). Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}(\alpha ,\beta )\subseteq  L]]></fr:tex>. In particular this means <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \pm \beta \in  L]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \beta \in  L]]></fr:tex> and when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta \neq 0]]></fr:tex> also <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha  / \beta \in  L]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p>Hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is a field and a subfield of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
